<p>What would be the cleanest way to run the PHP code below but instead of $_GET, using $_POST instead?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php function run_my_function() {     echo 'I just ran a PHP function!'; } if (isset($_GET['run'])) {     run_my_function(); } ?&gt; &lt;html&gt; &lt;body&gt;     &lt;p&gt;Hello there! &lt;a href="?run"&gt;Run a PHP function.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>